	Document(content="Question: Can anyone explain why the solution b = 3 + 0.1 ‚àó (0 ‚àí 1.0) √ó 20 = 1 uses (0 - 1)? All of the other problems I have done used (1 - 0.5) so I assumed this came from the threshold. Answer: $$\alpha=0.1, y=0$$$$x_1=20, x_2=2, x_3=5$$$$\beta_0=-1, \beta_1=3, \beta_2=-4, \beta_3=2$$The 1.0 comes from the prediction function $$P(x)$$, using the approximation $$\exp(t)=0$$ when $$t<-10$$ provided by the problem.$$P(x)=\frac{1}{1+\exp(-(\beta_0+\beta_1x_1+\beta_2x_2+\beta_3x_3))}=\frac{1}{1+\exp(-((-1)-+(3)(20)+(-4)(2)+(2)(5)))}=\frac{1}{1+\exp(-61)}\approx\frac{1}{1+0}=1.0$$$$\beta^1_1=\beta^0_1+\alpha*((y-P(x))\times x_1)=3+0.1*((0-1.0)\times20)=1$$", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'S24 Q5D', 'timestamp': '2024-12-13T20:13:24Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 135}),
