	Document(content="Question: I used this code to denoise my data¬†kpca = KernelPCA(kernel=\'rbf\', n_components= 64, fit_inverse_transform= True)X_train_denoised = kpca.fit_transform(X_train_poison_reshaped)X_test_denoised = kpca.transform(X_test_reshaped)allnumbers_denoised = kpca.transform(allnumbers_reshaped)And whatever I do, I cannot figure out why did the dimensions cut down to 61 instead of 64. I tried looking everywhere for an answer but it doesn\'t seem to work. I can\'t print out my denoised data because of the dimension and it\'s messing my models Answer: I think the dimension is indeed 64.¬†", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Denoised Data Dimensions using Kernel PCA (Mini Project Path #3)', 'timestamp': '2024-12-09T00:44:22Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 10}),
