	Document(content="Question: Hi, I just wanted to make sure that we will not lose points for receiving subpar results after running the models for our mini project. After running my model (I did option 1), the highest percent accuracy for one of the video prediction tests was about 25% (which is not great). In the readme file it states:I just want to validate that this is correct.¬† Answer: Yes, but you need to justify the results. In this case, you need to explain why the model could have such bad performance and support it with your evidence. Simply reporting the result is not enough.¬†", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Mini Project Results', 'timestamp': '2024-12-08T21:05:18Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 158}),
