	Document(content="Question: Hello,I got this output on my grading output for homework 8 that I was confused about:¬†Test case 2.4:input: 9_vidText.txt, 13_vidText.txt, 7_vidText.txt, 4_vidText.txt, 1_vidText.txtfunction tested : tfidf16 points - failed (code did not run)Your error = name \'tf\' is not definedchecking distinct(16 points):Test case 2.4:input: 9_vidText.txt, 13_vidText.txt, 7_vidText.txt, 4_vidText.txt, 1_vidText.txtfunction tested : distinct16 points - failed (code did not run)Your error = name \'tf\' is not definedI\'m not really sure why my code wouldn\'t run, seeing as it passed the test cases when I developed the code, and I made sure to use the correct variable and function names that were given. Any feedback would be appreciated, because I\'m not sure what happened.Thanks,Brandon Farber Answer: Please make a regrade request following the format posted on Piazza. It is much easier to get your submission and run from my side. If the error is trivial like wrong postion of the importation, you could get your points back :)", meta={'folders': ['hw8'], 'title': 'Confusion about grading output', 'timestamp': '2024-12-06T17:41:35Z', 'user': 'm0040vhe3t036j', 'tags': ['hw8', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 10}),
