	Document(content="Question: Hello!I have a few questions regarding the first question in path 1 of the mini project.¬†It states that we should run the prediction algorithm for each video individually. However, question 1 seems to imply that we should cluster with all videos together and sort it based on each individual behavior. So just to clarify my question: should we cluster for each behavior based off of each video one at a time, or should we cluster for each behavior for all videos all at once?For example (in case my wording is still a little confusing)---------------------------------------------------------------Variation 1:¬†Individual VideosVideo 1fracSpent clusters with datapoints only from video 1fracComp clusters with datapoints only from video 1¬†...etc.Video 2Video 3etc.Variation 2:¬†All videos togetherfracSpent clustersfracSpent datapoints from all videosfracComp clustersfracComp datapoints from all videosetc Answer: For k-means clustering, it needs a certain amount of data to form cluster by repeatedly calculating the centroid.¬†In your example, it is not clear to me why your would form \'clusters\' for each feature. The general logic is at the following:The dataset that we have right now: N * 11, N is the number of rows. And, dataset that we want to have: M * 11, M is the number videos watched by the students (students that completed at least 5 videos)Then, we want to build a k-means algorithm based on this M*11 dataset", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Mini Project Path 1 Question', 'timestamp': '2024-12-04T19:35:08Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 142}),
