	Document(content="Question: I am working on the second analysis question for path 1. I have done a regression model and am analyzing it\'s fit with the RSME and the R^2 value. My results for the R^2 are negative, which I know is not within acceptable range. I am having this issue for my model with just video watching features and the model with combined features and cluster labels. Is anyone else having this problem or do you have suggestions for what I should change to get a better R^2 value? Answer: I would suggest you to perform some sanity check on your fitted model. So, first thing you can try is to check the coefficients fitted from the data. See why it would give a such result. If you find some coefficients are extremely large or small, you can perform some normalization technique on the training dataset.¬†", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Path 1 R^2 value', 'timestamp': '2024-12-04T03:19:15Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 125}),
