	Document(content="Question: Hey, I am working on the miniproject and have chosen path 3. I am wondering if the noise scale of 10 that is given to us is correct. I plotted the images and they are so noisy it is hard to identify any digits. Denoising doesn\'t help either.The models consistently have accuracies below 50% after denoising attempts with different hyperparameter values. In contrast, when I try with a noise scale of 1, the results are more promising.Noisy images (noise scale = 1)Denoised imagesModel Performances:Gaussian model on denoised data is 0.6450417052826691K Nearest Neighbors model on denoised data is 0.9249304911955515MLP Classifier model on denoised data is 0.8294717330861909 Answer: Given you are asking part 8 (and rest of the parts), the question is not asking to what extent the model is robust to the \'poisoning\'. So, you do not need to change or tune the noise scale. As the question asked \'Described ...., Discuss ...\', you only need to present what you observed, what are your conclusions, and why this could happen.¬†", meta={'folders': ['project'], 'title': 'Path 3: Noise Scale', 'timestamp': '2024-11-26T21:50:12Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['project', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 145}),
