	Document(content="Question: what is the reason we are using 99.7% instead of 68 or 95%? Answer: because the z-score is calculated to be 3 and not 2 or 1. The z-score defines how many standard deviations away the quantity is from the mean. If we have a z of 3 that corresponds to 99.7%. A z of 2 is 95% and z=1 is 68%.", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'F22 exam 2 Q6 part C', 'timestamp': '2024-11-18T22:49:29Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 116}),
	Document(content="Question: I thought the answer was c, which is log(2/3). How come the answer is 0? Answer: idf is equal to log(N/n_t)¬† N is the total number of documents and n_t is the number of documents the term shows in. Since the term shows in all (both) documents. log(2/2) = log(1) = 0", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'F22 exam 2 - Q5 part C 2.', 'timestamp': '2024-11-18T21:59:24Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 107}),
	Document(content="Question: Can someone explain the step-by-step process for getting the answer to this question? Answer: y-hat = wx + by~ = w~ x + b~(y-hat - M)/S = y~ from normalization formula given on slides(wx +b - M)/S = w~ x + b~ from substitutionthen with algebra(b-M)/S = b~b = S*b~ + M and substitute back to solve for w as well(wx + S*b~ + M - M)/S = w~x + b~(wx)/S + b~ = w~x + b~wx/S = w~xw/S = w~S*w~ = w", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Fall 2022 Exam 2 - Question 6 Part D', 'timestamp': '2024-11-18T21:33:31Z', 'user': 'm02ppa1qyn92ki', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 103}),
