	Document(content="Question: For this question, what is the difference between (\.edu) and [\.edu], what is the difference between using brackets and parentheses?¬†Screenshot_2024-11-17_164600.png Answer: Parenthesis puts the contents into one group, which can be referenced later. To match this group, all characters must be matched in order. Brackets give a \'set\' of characters that can be chosen from to match, [abc] is equivalent to saying \'a|b|c\'.", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Q2 2022 Fall, Exam 2.', 'timestamp': '2024-11-17T21:57:02Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 127}),
