	Document(content="Question: Hello,In Homework 9, Problem 4, the concatenate_features() function, according to the README and comments, should output an array of shape **(2, n)**, but according to the README's expected outputs, should output an array of shape **(400, 2)**. Outputting the *former* shape makes the rest of the code work without changing the transposition in main(), but the *latter* is the result of using reshape and concatenate as described in the commented instructions (the former can be made in one line). Which is correct? Answer: The correct shape for concatenation is (2,n). So the output mentioned in the readme is wrong. It should be (2,400) instead. Thanks for pointing it out!", meta={'folders': ['hw9'], 'title': 'HW9 P4 - (2, n) or (n, 2) - and why four lines?', 'timestamp': '2024-11-02T16:47:12Z', 'user': 'k5bcz1dvnoa226', 'tags': ['hw9', 'student'], 'likes': 4, 'views': 170}),
	Document(content="Question: I get the following error when I try to run the problem two question. I cannot find the library grp, thus being unable to actually run the script or pip install it. What do I do? I have all of the other needed packages (numpy, helper, nltk)File \'. . .local-packages\Python39\site-packages\helper \\Unix.py\', line 7, in <module>¬† ¬† import grpModuleNotFoundError: No module named \'grp\' Answer: if you have a longer/ full stack trace that could help diagnose. Also, what are you programming on to get this error? grp is a UNIX-specific package which could be causing errors either because you are set up with too many packages or not enough. If you are on a Unix (linux) system then you might need to reinstall python properly for your system because grp is a native package which would be why pip doesn\'t grab it.", meta={'folders': ['hw8'], 'title': 'no module named \'grp\'??', 'timestamp': '2024-11-01T23:48:59Z', 'user': 'l70og4g46ob61k', 'tags': ['hw8', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 113}),
