	Document(content="Question: We are asked to plot y and y_hat with different colors (implying not relative to each other). What should we plot each relative to/against? X_goog is multidimensional with 6 features, so you cannot plot y and y_hat relative to it on a 2d plot, and the question does not specify one of the features to plot on the x-axis. Answer: You are not supposed to plot the feature. You are required to use the features to make the prediction (a single value) and compare that to the corresponding ground-truth. Yes, X is a 6 dim feature,so in that case you plot y¬† and y_hat against the sample index, i.e., you assign an index to each input sample. This way, each point (a single value) on the x-axis corresponds to a (6-dim) sample, with the y-values representing the actual and predicted outputs.¬†", meta={'folders': ['hw7'], 'title': 'HW7 Problem 2 Part 8', 'timestamp': '2024-10-28T20:36:29Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw7', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 105}),
