	Document(content="Question: Just to confirm the responses to @227 and @222.If the threshold is the default value (0), the dictionary entries are sorted in descending order of their values, and if the values are equal, in the descending order of their keys.On the other hand, if the threshold parameter is passed in, the dictionary entries are sorted in descending order of their values, and if the values are equal, in the ascending order of their keys.Is this correct as this is how the provided examples work. Answer: The ordering will be the same with/without the threshold parameter.¬†", meta={'folders': ['hw8'], 'title': 'HW8 Sorting Inconsistency Clarification', 'timestamp': '2024-10-26T04:09:18Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw8', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 159}),
