	Document(content="Question: For problem 2, hw6, homework readme says :4. If the above conditions are both not met, there is no match. You will then return a tuple of strings (\'noauthor\', \'noname\')in the provided testcase it is tested for:testcase26 = \'Khaled Hosseini wrote sad books\'print(\'Student answer: \',problem2(testcase26),\'\tAnswer correct?\', problem2(testcase26) == (\'nohero\', \'noname\'))where \'noauthor\' is replaced with \'nohero\'. is it an error or am I understanding the default case wrongly Answer: It is an error. The correct output should be (\'noauthor\', \'noname\'). You can correct the testcase.", meta={'folders': ['hw6'], 'title': 'problem 2 testcase 26', 'timestamp': '2024-10-04T20:00:07Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw6', 'student'], 'likes': 5, 'views': 182}),
