	Document(content="Question: Are we expected to utilize our code from HW 3 to accurately answer this question? Is it asking for the optimum bin-width,¬† or simply the size of the entire population provided via \'city_vehicle_survey.txt\'? Answer: For Problem 2, part 2 is asking for statistical tests(sample size, mean, standard error, test score (z or t), and p-value) regarding the given city_vehicle_survey.txt data. Part 3 is asking you to calculate the minimum sample size that would result in a p-value of 0.05.¬†This assignment does not require code from previous assignment.", meta={'folders': ['hw5'], 'title': 'HW5 Problem 2, Sample Size', 'timestamp': '2024-09-26T19:03:20Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw5', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 120}),
