	Document(content="Question: I am completing the write up portion of homework 5 and the text boxes on the document only allow me to write in one line, rather than carrying over, underneath the previous line. The font size keeps getting automatically adjusted to account for additional writing. As a result, the font is so small that now it is unreadable. Is there a way to edit the formatting of the text boxes so I can fully answer the questions and have my writing visible to the graders? Right now, the write up is opening in Edge and I can\'t find a way to open it in another browser or program. Answer: Try looking up an online PDF editor that you can upload the PDF to directly. Some allow you to change the font size in a textbox.", meta={'folders': ['hw5'], 'title': 'really tiny font on write up part of homework', 'timestamp': '2024-09-25T23:32:59Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw5', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 122}),
	Document(content="Question: I can write and save the pdf within VSC (Visual Studio Code), but it won\'t let me commit it or show changes anywhere else. I honestly don\'t know what to do I\'ve done the PDF and submitted it to Gradescope, I just cannot get it to work for Github. What should I do? Answer: You do need to upload it to GitHub. Try manually uploading the pdf from your desktop. Or see @115", meta={'folders': ['hw5'], 'title': 'Committing the PDF in VSC to Github Desktop to Github', 'timestamp': '2024-09-25T23:26:00Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw5', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 113}),
	Document(content="Question: When calculating the z-score is it z = mean - hypothesized mean / standard deviation OR z = hypothesized mean - mean / standard deviation¬†I‚Äôve seen it both ways so I‚Äôm just confused as to which we use for the assignment.¬† Answer: z = (sample mean - mean under null hypothesis) / standard error¬†For a two-tailed test, since p = 2*Normal_CDF(-|z|) is invariant to the sign of the z-score, your p-value calculation should hold either way.", meta={'folders': ['hw5'], 'title': 'HW 5 calculation of Z-score', 'timestamp': '2024-09-25T21:17:05Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw5', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 126}),
