	Document(content="Question: Going through the histogram section for hw 2 I‚Äôve run into an issue where when calculating the limits of the bin Ill get an extra small decimal attached to itExample:¬†Min_val = -1W =2.2Min_val + W = 1.200000000000000002And as a result 1.2 is included when it should be a part of the next bin.Any tips on how I can prevent this? Answer: I am not sure what precision the test cases are in but you probably could get away with solving this problem using the round() function. It takes the value you are rounding and a precision modifier so you can round it out to a large number of decimal points, but for this application, I think you can manage with like 5 or 6 decimal points of precision but floats can technically go to 17(?) or somewhere about. Because all our inputs are in integers for this problem rounding these values in this way shouldn\'t impact the outcome.", meta={'folders': ['hw2'], 'title': 'Problem with Float Addition (hw 2)', 'timestamp': '2024-09-03T16:47:17Z', 'user': 'ktnb6c7elcf740', 'tags': ['hw2', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 115}),
