	Document(content="Question: When will homework 1 grades be posted?¬† Answer: We are still discussing the final procedure for grading and re-grading. We expect to put out the final procedure by the end of next (or this) week.¬†Here is the tentative schedule for grading and regrading policies (we might change it later, please stay tuned for brightspace and piazza):After the homework is due:0-1 week: grading1-2 week: re-grade request from students2-3 week: regradingSo, it would be a 3-week cycle, which, after the homework is due, we will grade them within a week (due to the late submission policy), then students can have another week to review the solution and submit regrade request if you have any doubts. Then, in the following week, we will handle all the re-grading requests within the week.¬†", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'HW1 Grades', 'timestamp': '2024-09-01T17:04:13Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 157}),
	Document(content="Question: Github asks if I am planning to use my fork to contribute to the parent project or for my own purposes. Which one of these options should I choose for the homework? Answer: When you click the link to create a repository for the homework, that is the repository we grade. So use the one with your Purdue ID.", meta={'folders': ['other', 'hw2'], 'title': 'Github Question', 'timestamp': '2024-09-01T14:19:15Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw2', 'other', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 133}),
