	Document(content="Question: Good day,I was working on my homework and decided to clone my repository using Git. However, after running the `git clone` command, my terminal kept prompting me for my GitHub username and password. Even though I entered the correct credentials, the issue persisted. I then decided to change my GitHub password, but that didn\'t resolve the problem either.¬†This is what my terminal have been showing to me:alissultanabdirov@pal-nat186-148-168 ECE20875 % git clone https://github.com/ECEDataScience/homework-1-f24-aabdirov.gitCloning into \'homework-1-f24-aabdirov\'...Username for \'https://github.com\': aabdirovPassword for \'https://aabdirov@github.com\':remote: Support for password authentication was removed on August 13, 2021.remote: Please see https://docs.github.com/get-started/getting-started-with-git/about-remote-repositories#cloning-with-https-urls for information on currently recommended modes of authentication.fatal: Authentication failed for \'https://github.com/ECEDataScience/homework-1-f24-aabdirov.git/\'alissultanabdirov@pal-nat186-148-168 ECE20875 % Answer: I think you need to generate security tokens instead of using passwords. Please refer to Github Webpage for more information. After you have the token, use the token for the password prompt.", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Homework 1 username and password issue in the terminal', 'timestamp': '2024-08-26T21:40:40Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 17}),
	Document(content="Question: For homework 1, can we import the math library? Will this be penalized? Answer: I think the rule of thumb is that you would want to avoid importing any libraries that need to \'pip/conda install\' unless there are clear instructions in the handout. The reason is that the grading system might not have such libraries installed, which might cause your program to fail.¬†", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Importing different libraries?', 'timestamp': '2024-08-26T21:12:20Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 150}),
	Document(content="Question: Hello,¬†I was wondering if this message meant I did something incorrectly, I didn\'t see this in this in the video for Git and I wanted to confirm if I had done the git steps correctly. My code from VSC updated correctly in the repository so I just wanted to make sure this was correct.¬† Answer: Make sure you are committing only to the main branch of your own forked repository. The above message only shows what changes have been made/committed since from only version of the repository. You don\'t have to Contribute or Sync fork. This message above can be ignored.", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Github Message - This Branch is one commit ahead of main', 'timestamp': '2024-08-26T16:36:43Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 150}),
	Document(content="Question: I took a look online to look at why my code for problem 1 wasn\'t giving me the result I was looking for and stack Overflow had a pretty simple fix for my issue.I have used stack for personal projects in the past and I was just wondering if consulting it was acceptable or it would be preferred to not look at it at all?If anybody knows the answer, let me know Answer: I think, for homework, you could search for relevant information online. However, you cannot directly \'copy and paste\' the exact code/solution, which will be considered plagiarism. The better way is to understand the logic behind any material and then write down the code/solution yourself.¬†", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Can we consult stack?', 'timestamp': '2024-08-26T02:30:23Z', 'user': 'm02vbtvh4t51y2', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 150}),
	Document(content="Question: I would like to ask if the date of the final exam has been determined? Answer: As per the Office of the Registrar \'The final exam schedule will be available in late September for the fall term.\'¬†", meta={'folders': ['exam'], 'title': 'Date of final exam', 'timestamp': '2024-08-25T03:01:45Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['exam', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 168}),
	Document(content="Question: If we wanted to solve a problem recursively and integrate an additional function into the program as long as the correct solution comes out of the problem function it would be ok right? Answer: almost certainly would be alright. I used a helper function. As long as ‚Äúpython3 problems.py‚Äù produces the correct output I can‚Äôt think of any issues. Confirm with the instructor though¬†", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Homework 1 question', 'timestamp': '2024-08-25T00:55:16Z', 'user': 'lzndecmigcy4fq', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 162}),
	Document(content="Question: I do not need to push my virtual environment to github right? Answer: Yes, that is correct. Homework assignments will specify what files should be included in your submission in the ‚ÄúWhat you need to submit‚Äù section on the README. You should not need to push anything other than the specified files.", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Virtual environment', 'timestamp': '2024-08-24T01:16:28Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 154}),
	Document(content="Question: Hello,It was mentioned during yesterday\'s class that today the first homework would appear available. I saw that the links would be available through bright space and piazza. I was just wondering if it\'s already been released or not? Just wanted to double check to make sure I\'m not missing anything. Answer: See @13", meta={'folders': ['hw1'], 'title': 'Accessing First Homework', 'timestamp': '2024-08-23T14:05:58Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['hw1', 'student'], 'likes': 5, 'views': 180}),
	Document(content="Question: When trying to access Jupyter Hub through RCAC, it says you can log in using your Purdue Login, but when I use my information it says that it is invalid. Is there a different login I should be using?¬† Answer: Not the answer you are looking for, but I would suggest using VSC (Visual Studio Code) as your code editor because it supports a lot of languages, has tons of features, is very customizable, and easy to use.", meta={'folders': ['other'], 'title': 'Accessing Jupyter Hub', 'timestamp': '2024-08-22T19:01:01Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['other', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 170}),
	Document(content="Question: The syllabus says that, for programming assignments, all programs should run correctly in the versions of Python available on the Scholar cluster. How do I make sure my programs are in a correct Python version? Answer: Probably just make sure its Python 3 rather than Python 2. Beyond that, some libraries struggle using some specific versions (i.e. 3.12). To check you python version locally, use some variant of \'python --version\' in the terminal or shell.", meta={'folders': ['other'], 'title': 'Python Version', 'timestamp': '2024-08-22T15:04:40Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['other', 'student'], 'likes': 0, 'views': 170}),
	Document(content="Question: I\'ve registered for a GitHub account and filled out the form letting the instructors know what my account is so my grades can be synched to Brightspace. I clicked on the link provided in the syllabus, in an attempt to join the ECE 20875 GitHub classroom, and was taken to a GitHub page for classrooms. However, a classroom for ECE 20875 does not appear and it looks like I haven\'t joined the classroom. Currently, GitHub says I have no classrooms.How can I join the classroom so I am able to complete assignments? Answer: There‚Äôs no need to join any GitHub Classroom directly. Instead, please follow these steps to ensure you‚Äôre ready for the assignments:1. Set up your GitHub account: If you don‚Äôt already have one, please create a GitHub account as soon as possible. Don‚Äôt forget to complete the GitHub username Google form linked in the syllabus.¬†¬†2. Watch for assignment links: For each homework, we‚Äôll provide a specific GitHub Classroom link. You‚Äôll use these links to access and submit your assignments.Please make sure your GitHub account is set up and keep an eye on both Piazza and Brightspace for the assignment links, which will be shared when each homework is released.", meta={'folders': ['other'], 'title': 'Join GitHubClassroom?', 'timestamp': '2024-08-22T03:59:38Z', 'user': '', 'tags': ['other', 'student'], 'likes': 1, 'views': 172}),
